  "abstract": "Finger millet germplasm pool remains largely uncharacterised, thus a constraint to\r\nfinding genetically diverse germplasm with beneficial traits for use in breeding\r\nprogrammes. A composite collection of 1000 accessions, which also consists of 622 core\r\ncollection accessions (Upadhyaya et al. 2006), has been developed and molecularly\r\nprofiled using 20 SSRs (Dida et al. 2007) in high throughput assay (ABI3700).",
